>> WriteChunkyPixels() doesn't exist in KS3.0.  On your system you're
>> probably just lucky that attempts to call it appear to return without
>> doing any damage.
>>
>Really? i tought it was writechunkypixels8() that didn't exist.

Sorry I haven't heard of writechunkypixels8().

WritePixelArray8() was introduced in KS2.04 (or thereabouts).  However
it is deficient in that it assumes the source width is the same as the
dest bitmap width.  So it can't be used for "direct rectangles" in
Quake.  The alternative of calling WritePixelLine8() for every pixel
row is possible, but that would add lots of slow context switches to
the PPC version.

WriteChunkyPixels() was introduced in KS3.1 to overcome the deficiency
of WritePixelArray8().

Cybergraphics.library has WritePixelArray(), which has all the
functionality of WriteChunkyPixels() plus the ability to render
15/16/24-bit pixels.  It can be used on KS3.0, but only if
cybergraphics.library is open.

