@node 08049.004
Subject: Re: Re: Perspective Mapping
From: Thomas Frieden <tfrieden@uni-trier.de>
Date: Fri, 14 Jan 2000 21:11:02 +0100 (CET)

Hi,

On Fri, 14 Jan 2000, Micha!? wrote:
> PopUp is an unwanted effect on the PSX, when a polygon get drawed that you can
> see it, it has /popped up/.
> BTW: Isn't this a PSX-HW-problem?

No, it's also possible with other hardware, even in software rendering.
The problem pops up (so to speak :) when you do not draw "deep" enough.
Normally, you would draw far-away polygons only if they cover a certain
pixel-area on the screen. In racing games, you draw everything up to a
certain distance. But, if polygons beyond this distance are already very
large when they come into view, they appear to pup up suddenly. This is
not only related to the playstation. Many games try to hide that by
fogging, to reduce the viewing distance, or (to stick to racing games) by
making the tracks very curvy, so you don't see far ahead.

CU, 
