>slow.  Even the ppc ones.  Maybe they just a delay loop in them somake them
>that slow though :)

People, always differentiate between StormMesa *with* hardware acceleration
and *without*. Many programs by default don't use 3d hardware with
StormMesa, if some effects aren't supported exactly. To bypass these
problems there are some variables (i.e. MESA/FAST) which forces programs
to use hardware acceleration even if some effects aren't exactly
supported.

To find out whether hardware was used, the env variable MESA/STATS should
be set to 1. In this case, statistical information is printed out to
the shell, when hardware is used, or some failure reasons are printed,
if hardware wasn't used. If nothing is printed, then no hardware was
used.

